@node 22 "Introduction"

     The first time you may have heard about a small white ghost and a bubble was ten years ago.
Actually, Bubble ghost was a commercial game published in 1987 by ERE Informatique. We decided to
make a new game using the original Bubble ghost concept. After all, nobody hesitates to remake
a @{b}Pacman@{ub} or a @{b}BoulderDash@{ub}. Perhaps it is the opportunity to introduce a new classic.

     However this game is original as all the code, musics, sounds, grafics and the design were
created by @{i}ANONYM SOFTWARE@{ui}.
     This game is a shareware because nothing was physically taken from the original of 1987.
     SBR is a whole new game and the result of hard months of work for us.


   @{b}SUPER BUBBLE REMIX @{ub} stands (with many other things) for

                   - A 40 levels challenge.
                   - A lot of monsters and vicious traps.
                   - A well-coded game in @{b}AMOS@{ub}.
                   - An overscan game (320X288).
                   - A total of 8 musix and plenty of sound effects.
                   - A lot of options and a system of codes.

   Don't be surprised if you discovered details or references to different games such as @{b}SUPERFROG@{ub},
@{b}RICK DANGEROUS@{ub}, @{b}TURRICAN@{ub}...

@endnode

